<TEXT>
robert n mcclory former representative and 
illinois republican thrust into the national spotlight for his role 
in impeachment proceedings against president richard nixon died 
sunday he was 80 
mcclory was elected to the illinois house of representatives in 
1950 he served in the state senate from 1952 to 1962 he was the 
secondranking republican on the house judiciary committee during 
congressional hearings on the breakin at the democratic national 
committee headquarters in the watergate complex in washington 
mcclory was one of the leading house supporters of an article of 
impeachment in 1974 charging nixon with abusing his constitutional 
powers in the watergate matter he drafted another article charging 
the president with contempt of congress for resisting subpoenas 
</TEXT>
