mrs phillips was the mother of capt mark phillips who in 1973 
married anne the only daughter of queen elizabeth ii 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
james wesley silver 81 whose book critical 
of white supremacy in mississippi led to his dismissal from the 
university of missisippi faculty in the 1960s died monday 
silver came to ole miss as a history professor in 1936 and left 
in 1965 at the request of the universitys board of trustees 
following publication of mississippi a closed society 
the book explored the racial divisions in mississippi and 
sharply criticized the states white political establishment for 
hanging on to visions of confederate glories silver wrote five 
other books edmund pendleton gaines confederate mississippi 
and church propaganda a life for the confederacy 
mississippi in the confederacy and running scared silver in 
mississippi 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
heinz r pagels physicist executive 
director of the new york academy of sciences and adjunct professor 
at the rockefeller university was killed saturday in a 
mountainclimbing accident he was 49 
pagels began his academic career at the rockefeller university 
in 1966 and left as an associate professor in 1983 to become the 
executive director and chief executive officer of the new york 
academy of sciences 
he was a theoretical physicist working in the area of 
relativistic quantum field theory and cosmology and the author of 
three books including the cosmic code perfect symmetry 
and dreams of reason pagels was also a former board member of 
the aspen physics institute 
</TEXT>
