the turnover was the fifth since retired gen john w vessey 
acting as a special presidential envoy reached an agreement in 
hanoi a year ago under which vietnam would accelerate the search 
for remains especially several dozen on washingtons top priority 
list 
this weeks talks were agreed upon during a meeting at the 
untied nations on june 8 between vessey and vietnamese foreign 
minister nguyen co thach 
the us technical team was led by lt col joe harvey of the 
us embassys joint casualty resolution center and joined by 
representatives from the us army central identification 
laboratory based in hawaii the official said 
we look forward to the results of the july 2528 meeting 
between technical representatives we hope progress can be made 
quickly on resolving this longstanding problem of concern to the 
powmia families of us and american people the official quoted 
us state department spokeswoman phyllis oakley as saying thursday 
in washington 
since the war ended vietnam has returned more than 150 sets of 
remains that the army laboratory has confirmed as americans 
vietnam says it has returned the remains of 241 missing americans 
and information on 45 others whose remains were determined to be 
no longer in existence 
