so far 140 of the 151 governments that own the bank have 
decided to contribute among the other countries that have not made 
a pledge are algeria cambodia vietnam and south yemen 
president reagan has urged approval of the contribution it has 
been held up in congress by disagreement over what should be done 
to handle the bulk of the third worlds 12 trillion debt 
last year the bank got back more in repayments and interest from 
third world borrowers than it gave them in new loans bank 
officials want to reverse that trend and increase lending to well 
over 20 billion a year in the early 1990s 
our influence and leadership within the bank are certainly at 
stake and i would raise the question if the united states is 
not going to participate in capital increases whether the bank 
itself can survive over a long period of time volcker told a 
news conference 
he added that the bank could continue lending for a year or two 
without new capital the united states as the biggest shareholder 
is expected to furnish more than 18 percent 
but against the prospect of not getting their capital 
replenished it is not in the nature of the beast and would not be 
