cambodias warring parties held peace 
talks monday for the first time but they apparently made no 
progress on negotiating an end to the countrys civil war 
the two central problems to be tackled are the future of the 
communist khmer rouge guerrillas and organizing elections for a new 
cambodian government 
although we have not solved any concrete problems each side 
has revealed its position to the other side said cambodian prime 
minister hun sen after talks with the three guerrilla groups which 
oppose his vietnameseinstalled government 
the four cambodian leaders gathered in the summer palace of the 
