new regulations announced monday by the 
agriculture department will allow horse shows for all breeds to 
continue said a senator who had monitored the developments 
the negotiations have been long and complex said sen mitch 
mcconnell rky but i think everyone has emerged a winner 
horse shows for many breeds were closed earlier this year after 
the american horse protection association filed a lawsuit seeking 
enforcement of regulations primarily for walking horses that had 
adversely affected much of the industry 
the regulations approved monday permanently replace interim 
rules that had been imposed to allow the continuation of horse 
shows while the regulations were being negotiated 
major provisions of the new regulations include a new uniform 
standard for pads that would apply to all horse breeds new rules 
on pad material rejection of a proposal by usda to further limit 
the weight of horseshoes and new guidelines on examination 
procedures for horses exhibited in walking horse shows 
the usda had solicited comments in april on the interim 
regulations during the last several months mcconnell sponsored 
negotiations with major horse organizations addressed by the usda 
interim rules 
the negotiations resulted in a joint comment on behalf of over 
100 national horses organizations being sent to agriculture 
secretary richard lyng in the letter the organizations 
recommended the new regulations adopted monday 
these recommendations were reached after weeks of negotiations 
with every major horse organization throughout the country 
mcconnell said in a statement released by his office now that 
the regulations are permanent horse shows throughout kentucky and 
the nation can continue without the fear of being shut down 
