the birth of louise brown was the first time that science and 
medicine had really come into human conception and clarified all 
the problems and all the mysteries of human conception 
now we have a lot of information success rates are going 
up with the use of frozen embryos together with better fertility 
drugs and the cost is going down because newer simpler 
techiques of collecting eggs are making the approach far more 
simple 
