devised the technique originally to treat women with blocked 
fallopian tubes 
in vitro fertilization has helped produce thousands of babies 
worldwide but the technique remains costly and uncertain of 
success and is available to only about 5 percent of childless 
couples 
most people do not get pregnant with the technique 
edwards said 
