<DOCNO> AP880725-0197 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
when the sirroco blows up the adriatic from 
the deserts of libya venices lagoon swells up and spills into the 
city sirens sound a mournful reminder venice is losing its 
struggle with the environment 
even at the height of summer gondoliers ply their trade over 
murky green and often foulsmelling canals alive with algae 
thriving on tons of raw sewage 
but a group of scientists and engineers are finally preparing to 
test the prototype of a system to protect venice from the sea that 
once protected it 
after nearly four years of work and 700 million in costs the 
engineers in the fall will install at the lido entrance to the 
venice lagoon the prototype of a mobile dike designed to stem the 
flood tides that have troubled the citys past and threaten its 
future 
the goal of the project is to save venice to save the life of 
the lagoon to save the port to save the historic city and the 
economic life of its people said maurio fabris director of 
public relations for the venezia nuova new venice consortium 
he said the consortium of 26 italian companies is executing the 
10year 44 billionproject to build a line of mobile dikes 
across the lagoons three entrances shore up the sea walls and 
islands preserve the canals and restore the ecological balance in 
the polluted lagoon 
venetians built their island city along 150 winding canals to 
protect themselves from invaders now the threat comes from the sea 
that once guarded them 
high tides flood the city about 100 times a year corroding 
magnificent churches monuments and the marble walls of elegant 
villas 
the consortium intends to stem the tides with the mobile dikes 
strung across the bottom of the lagoon entrances during flood 
tides fabris said engineers will raise the dikes effectively 
sealing the lagoon ships will be able to sail in and out through a 
series of locks at the entrances 
with the mobile system we will be able to decide at what point 
and at what time we want to intervene said fabris 
flood tides are triggered by differences in atmospheric pressure 
at either end of the adriatic or by the sirocco wind blowing across 
the mediterranean and up the adriatic driving the sea water 
northward toward venice 
great flood tides were heavily destructive to venice in 789 in 
1268 and in 1280 in 1410 they killed close to 1000 people in 
this century the worst floods came in 1916 1936 1951 and in 
1966 when high water caused an estimated 85 million damage 
venetians have struggled for centuries to protect the city from 
its surroundings these efforts have included building sea walls to 
guard the littoral islands and several antisilting projects 
more recently they succeeded in stopping venice from sinking 
after it had settled 4 inches from 1926 to 1970 by banning 
industrial use of underground water 
critics say the government and the new consortium have reacted 
slowly to venices problems that the city has been drowning in a 
sea of bureacracy and empty talk 
the consortiums fabris responds that the law creating the 
project requires that all the work be experimentally tested 
reversible if necessary and done in stages 
scientists used satellite analysis and computer models to study 
how their work will effect the problems of stagnation and erosion 
scale models of the entire lagoon and the three entrances were 
built at italys hydraulic experimental center in nearby padua 
in september workers will install the prototype of one of the 
56foothigh 66footlong mobile dikes for six to eight months of 
tests 
fabris said the consortium will be ready to put the entire line 
of dikes in place by 1992 
he added that the tests indicate that engineers will be able to 
help wash pollutants out of the lagoon 
as part of the project the government is also supposed to enact 
laws restricting the dumping of industrial pollutants and the use 
of agricultural pesticides that seep into the lagoon 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

