exxon corp the nations largest oil company 
today reported a 4 percent increase in secondquarter net income as 
higher refining and chemicals earnings offset lower exploration and 
production results 
exxon said it earned 12 billion or 90 cents a share up from 
net income of 115 billion or 81 cents a share in the second 
quarter of 1987 
revenue for the quarter rose 7 percent to 2163 billion from 
2016 billion a year ago 
exxon chairman lg rawl noted that margins were stronger as 
supply costs dropped and product prices firmed during the 
quarter he also said increased demand for petroleum products 
boosted sales volume in both the united states and abroad 
earnings from exploration and production operations totaled 703 
million 183 million less than the yearago period the company 
noted that lower crude oil sales to its own refineries as well as 
to outside customers coupled with higher expenses to offset 
increased crude production from new and expanded oil fields 
the companys chemicals operation reported an 89 million 
increase in earnings to 314 million while higher copper prices 
helped the coal and minerals unit report net income of 8 million 
compared with a 14 million loss a year ago 
exxon reported corporate and financing charges of 172 million 
up from 24 million a year go 
for the first six months exxon reported net income of 266 
billion or 196 a share up 20 percent from 222 billion or 
156 a share in the first half of 1987 
revenue during the period totaled 4363 billion up 10 percent 
from revenue of 396 billion in the yearago period 
