mattels wood with children often choosing what they see on 
television for instance a miniature version of the white ferrari 
testarossa driven in miami vice is one of the most popular toy 
sellers 
the children show some loyalty toward americanmade cars walsh 
says because thats what they often see on the streets that 
loyalty can carry over into their adulthood he said 
if they happen to like fourwheeldrive cars as a kid theres 
a strong possibility theyll like fourwheel vehicles as an 
adult walsh said in my opinion if you like a particular type 
of car as a kid youre apt to grow up and like them 
thats good news for detroit automakers who usually charge no 
royalties to miniature automakers who replicate their cars 
