more than 190 a bushel over six consecutive losing sessions 
light scattered showers fell during the weekend and monday in 
the midwest continuing a pattern that developed in midjuly to 
replace the unusually warm and dry conditions that had dominated 
the region during the previous three months 
there is certainly a lot of varying opinion over how much 
benefit it may have done for the crop but traders clearly are 
