bumble bee seafoods inc a privately held san diegobased producer 
of canned seafood with annual revenue of 265 million pillsbury 
also said it had decided to sell off its grain merchandising 
division and use the proceeds to finance the bumble bee acquisition 
in prepared statement spoor said that attracting a topflight 
chief executive has been a major priority he called smith a 
gifted and capable leader who has the unanimous support of our 
board of directors and the senior management 
analysts have been critical of pillsbury saying it lacked clear 
and vital leadership over the past few years 
its aftertax profit plummeted 62 percent in fiscal 1988 to 
693 million on sales of 62 billion largely because of a 
restructuring charge associated with the sale of the godfathers 
pizza chain and a number of other restaurant operations and 
consolidations 
the restaurant unit which accounts for nearly half of the 
companys total revenue reported a 5 percent drop in sales in the 
fiscal year ended may 31 as burger king continued to lose market 
share to rival mcdonalds corp 
pillsburys weakness has been more related to restaurants and 
if they got a guru in restaurants they may have been better off 
said edward froelich an analyst at pershing amp co 
