its exciting and challenging opportunities he said 
the 65yearold spoor returned to the helm at pillsbury after 
the ouster of john stafford whom spoor had groomed as his 
successor and who presided over pillsburys first earnings decline 
in 16 years spoor had run the company from 1973 through 1985 
speculation had been swirling on wall street recently that 
despite its difficulties pillsbury might be a takeover target 
but analysts are divided as to how attractive a takeover 
candidate pillsbury may be carnes for instance said pillsbury 
had too many wrecks in the ditch right now 
