shareholders of indian head calls for fleetnorstar to exchange 
1775 shares of its common stock for each of indian heads 47 
million shares of common stock outstanding 
the exchange ratio represents a price of about 4437 for each 
indian head share based on fleetnorstars closing price of 25 a 
share on friday the companies said in a statement 
the exchange of indian head convertible preferred stock into an 
equal number of fleetnorstar convertible preferred shares would 
boost the total value of the deal about 240 million the banks 
stated 
they said that price is approximately 17 times indian heads 
book value per common share and is a 30 percent premium over its 
market price based on its close on friday at 3425 a share 
indian head banks based in nashua has assets of about 18 
billion fleetnorstars assets are about 25 billion 
fleetnorstar has dual headquarters in providence ri and 
albany ny 
indian head has 46 branches throughout new hampshire and earned 
166 million in 1987 the company said 
